# No Unnecessary Abstractions

- Do not extract variables, helper functions, local components, or schema constants unless they are reused or clearly improve readability.
- Inline single-use validators directly in `inputValidator(...)`.
- Inline one-off mappings, constants, and helpers when they are only used once and are still readable.
- Prefer flatter files over premature abstraction.
- Follow the existing code shape in nearby files before introducing new structure.
